        "title": "What if URI path does not meet regex in Jax-RS",
        "body": "<p>I have a JAX-RS resource, where I use GET on a user on a specific ID, I have used a regex pattern to match, that the URI only accepts digits. But would happened, if something else was entered, would it just throw an exception, because, if the method, did not found anything anyway wouldn't it be the same?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> @GET\n@Path(\"/{id: [0-9]+}\") // pattern to only match numbers between 0-9, but what would happen without it?\npublic Response getUser(@PathParam(\"id\") int id) throws UserNotFoundException\n{\n    User   user    = userFacade.get(id);\n    String jsonDTO = gson.toJson(UserDTO.basic(user));\n    return Response.ok(jsonDTO).build();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
